com.code.aon.common.event
Class ManagerBeanListenerSupport

java.lang.Object
  com.code.aon.common.event.ManagerBeanListenerSupport
All Implemented Interfaces:
IManagerBeanListener
public class ManagerBeanListenerSupport
extends java.lang.Object
implements IManagerBeanListener

This is a utility class that can be used by IManagerBean classes that support CRUD after operations. You can use an instance of this class as a member field of your bean and delegate various work to it.

addListener

public void addListener(IManagerBeanListener listener)
Add a IManagerBeanListener to the listener list. The same listener object may be added more than once, and will be called as many times as it is added.

Parameters:
listener -

removeListener

public void removeListener(IManagerBeanListener listener)
Remove a IManagerBeanListener from the listener list. This removes a IManagerBeanListener that was registered. If listener was added more than once to the same event source, it will be notified one less time after being removed.

Parameters:
listener -
